snippet.textDisplay:
I started a month ago, and I just finished the game for the first time! I completely agree with all the comments praising this trailer because it‚Äôs truly special and stands out in the current gaming industry. I‚Äôm not sure who exactly made the trailer or who was responsible for blending 'Danzig - Mother' into it (sorry for not checking), but this sequence is exactly what I‚Äôve been wishing to see from the gaming industry for a long time. It‚Äôs so epic that I get goosebumps every time I watch it - that‚Äôs how much I love it! Thanks so much to whoever made it! 

I keep coming back to it whenever I hear Danzig on the Spotify, and I‚Äôm so thankful for this piece of art. The game itself is great too. It has its issues, but I had way too much fun playing it. Soon, I‚Äôll post a small video on my channel as a hobbyist way of showing how much I liked it. If you haven‚Äôt played the game yet, I highly recommend it! üî•

snippet.textDisplay:
best game in the souls universum, i have never played a soulsborn so often from the beginning to end! im absolutely addicted to this game. i have also very much fun with the multiplayer mode. i have only 3 negative point to make. 1. the latency in the multiplayer mode is often too high and you have no chance for a good fight. but still very funny. and i have to say, i hate it, that you cant talk to the people. i met people in the game, helped with a boss and stayed, me and this guy played over 4 hours together! it was so much fun, but i had too go. it would have very cool too meet the guy next day and play more, but how should i find him? sorry i drifted away a bit. so 2. point is this snap on enemy thing is not good. and 3. the enemy viraity is weak. the game has a lot of weapons and stuff too wear. but there should be more different enemys in different areas.
but i tell you, i played just every soulsborn and loved it, but lords of the fallen, for me personally is the best and most fun, a bit more then elden ring, not much. but still i think its a bit better.

snippet.textDisplay:
I know the original game wasn't well-received, but I enjoyed it enough to beat it a few times, and I saw the dna for a really special game in there. So, two things, I guess.
1: Yay, you get a chance to make that really special game!
B: Why did you name this sequel in such a was that will make the original game much harder to find in search engines? It feels like a deliberate attempt to bury the first game.

B: Why did you name this sequel in such a was that will make the original game much harder to find in search engines? It feels like a deliberate attempt to bury the first game.

snippet.textDisplay: This cinematic trailer looks really cool, but I certainly hope they borrow more from dark souls than the original LotF did. The first game was super clunky and really relied on the player doing specific things for certain enemies more like legend of zelda, mandatory block timings, certain spells or items needed, and a lot of useless consumables. I honestly feel like if they go more for the RPG elements and character building and really nail it being linear instead of super open world trying to be Elden Ring, then this could really be a great game for the next year.
snippet.textOriginal: This cinematic trailer looks really cool, but I certainly hope they borrow more from dark souls than the original LotF did. The first game was super clunky and really relied on the player doing specific things for certain enemies more like legend of zelda, mandatory block timings, certain spells or items needed, and a lot of useless consumables. I honestly feel like if they go more for the RPG elements and character building and really nail it being linear instead of super open world trying to be Elden Ring, then this could really be a great game for the next year.

snippet.textDisplay:
As always, something truly great will inspire others to try the same.

The Dark Souls series has slowly established itself; first as a very niche gaming experience, then as something generally accepted and acclaimed.

We are now seeing a plethora of games trying to emulate what Dark Souls did. Its combat style, Its gothic aesthetics, its dark knight theme, and its imposing boss fights, are all elements that are beginning to appear almost "as is" in other games.

But even if the dark atmosphere and gameplay experience are represented as best as possible by those who would try to replicate the masterfully crafted games, it is always the soul of the game that is harder to bring forward.

Maters of all domains have always given us original and deeply satisfying experiences through their creations, and the rest of us pick up what we can, but the essence of their success stays invisible and impossible to copy. The soul of a masterpiece game cannot be equal to the sum of its visible parts.

But let's hope the industry will learn well, and bring us superb games like From Software did.

snippet.textDisplay: So, I liked the first game.  I never finished it but didn't hate it as much as a lot of people do.  I know it's not as good as Dark Souls and other games made by the same company.  I liked the overall look of everything and the fact that it tried to have some kind of story.  But this trailer here makes me excited.  The function of the lamp seems to work like your Ghost does in Destiny, reviving you after death.  I hope we get to make our own character, but if we don't I'm also fine with it as long as the main character and the game are good.  Do we know if there is multiplayer(nevermind, just looked, there is co-op)?  I liked the line at the top of the picture at the end, and I am too daring to hope.  I don't expect Elden Ring, but I am definitely hoping for all of us and the people that made this that the game is good.  I will be checking it out.  Take care everyone out there.
